{"questionId":"d7afa874-519b-4f1b-b45f-1c75ea45613b_13","correctAnswer":"40","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Translate to equations","content":"From $27\\%$ of $h=24\\%$ of $j$, $h=\\tfrac{24}{27}j$. Also $j=\\tfrac{45}{100}k$."},{"title":"Combine the ratios","content":"Substituting gives $$h=\\tfrac{24}{27}\\cdot\\tfrac{45}{100}k=\\tfrac{1080}{2700}k.$$"},{"title":"Convert to a percent","content":"That is $\\tfrac{1080}{27}\\%=40\\%$ of $k$. The answer is <strong>40</strong>."}]}